        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "No SceneKit features depend directly on this direction's definitionâ€”it's simply a natural consequence of recognizing \"forward\" and \"up\" directions for use with cameras, directional lighting, and relative orientation operations."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This vector is always "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "(1, 0, 0)"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " for all nodes, but you can use this class property when it's convenient to refer to directions symbolically."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
